The paper deals with the problem of determining rank loss conditions for a concatenation of full-rank matrices with random coefficients, which has applications in wireless interference management and recommendation systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. The paper also uses tools from matroid and graph theories, which are commonly used in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses an application to topological interference management, which involves numerical analysis and optimization, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
